  "body": "Bright, light chicken and vegetable rice bowl with a lemon-herb finish. It’s designed as a microwave-friendly lunch: juicy chicken, crisp-tender vegetables, and just enough olive oil to stay satisfying without feeling heavy.\n\nPrep time: 35 minutes.\nEquipment: large saucepan with lid, large nonstick skillet, cutting board, sharp knife, spatula, and 1-2 lunch containers.\n\n1. Rinse {dry jasmine rice} and cook it in plenty of water according to the package method, **10-12 min** simmering, then **5 min** resting off the heat. Fluff with a fork.\n2. While the rice cooks, slice the {raw chicken breast} into thin strips. Toss with {garlic}, {dried oregano}, salt, and black pepper.\n3. Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat for **1 min**. Add half of the {extra virgin olive oil}, then the chicken. Sear **4 min** without moving, turn it, and cook **3-4 min** more until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a plate.\n4. Add the remaining {extra virgin olive oil} to the same skillet. Add the {zucchini} and {red bell pepper} and cook, stirring often, for **4-5 min** until crisp-tender. Add the {baby spinach} and cook **30-45 sec** until just wilted.\n5. Return the chicken and any juices to the pan, squeeze over the juice of the {lemon}, and toss everything together for **30 sec**. Taste and add a little more salt and black pepper if needed.\n6. Divide the {dry jasmine rice} between meal-prep containers, top with the chicken and vegetables, and spoon any pan juices over the top. Let cool for a few minutes before sealing.\n\nStorage: refrigerate for up to 3 days. It also freezes well for up to 2 months, though the spinach will be softer after thawing.\nReheating: microwave covered for 2-3 minutes, stirring halfway through. Add a small splash of water if the rice looks dry.\nTip: for an even fresher lunch, pack an extra lemon wedge and squeeze it over the bowl after reheating. If you want more volume, add an extra handful of spinach without changing the flavor much."
}

